Smallest mus size: 3

Setting (1, 6) is not 4 because:

  • (1, 6) and (1, 8) cannot both be 4 as they are both in row 1
  • (1, 6) and (2, 7) cannot both be 4 as they are both seperated by kings move
  • Some cell the cage starting at top-left position (0,6) must be 4 (Choices are: (1, 8), (2, 7))

Smallest mus size: 3

Setting (2, 5) is not 4 because:

  • (2, 5) and (3, 3) cannot both be 4 as they are both seperated by knights move
  • (2, 5) and (3, 4) cannot both be 4 as they are both the cage starting at top-left position (0,3)
  • Some cell in row 3 must be 4 (Choices are: (3, 3), (3, 4))
